1
00:02:02,299 --> 00:02:03,120
I say, Professor Fan.

2
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:04,420
Why are you always distancing yourself from the masses?

3
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:06,500
Why are you always distancing yourself from the masses?

4
00:02:06,859 --> 00:02:08,219
You're labeling me right from the start.

5
00:02:08,219 --> 00:02:09,819
How am I distancing myself from the masses?

6
00:02:09,939 --> 00:02:11,039
Look, let me count the ways for you.

7
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:13,300
You don't join the choir.

8
00:02:14,340 --> 00:02:15,740
You don't sign up for the sports meet.

9
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:18,500
You don't learn ballroom dancing.

10
00:02:18,979 --> 00:02:20,020
You don't attend the art class.

11
00:02:20,860 --> 00:02:22,659
Anything related to group activities,

12
00:02:22,659 --> 00:02:23,580
you don't participate in.

13
00:02:24,259 --> 00:02:26,500
Last time everyone at Evergreen Residence caught a cold,

14
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,699
and you were the only one who didn't.

15
00:02:27,819 --> 00:02:29,620
Tell me, aren't you out of touch with the masses?

16
00:02:29,659 --> 00:02:30,900
So catching a cold

17
00:02:30,979 --> 00:02:32,379
counts as a group activity to you?

18
00:02:32,379 --> 00:02:33,139
Alright.

19
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:34,539
Stop reading.

20
00:02:34,539 --> 00:02:36,539
All you do is read books all day long.

21
00:02:36,539 --> 00:02:38,539
As if you're so learned.

22
00:02:38,780 --> 00:02:39,860
What do you mean "as if"?

23
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,259
I am learned.

24
00:02:41,259 --> 00:02:42,180
Learned, huh?

25
00:02:42,819 --> 00:02:43,740
Then let me ask you a question.

26
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:44,539
Do you dare to answer?

27
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,259
I wouldn't dare.

28
00:02:45,819 --> 00:02:46,819
Yeah, right.

29
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:48,819
With those little questions of yours.

30
00:02:49,099 --> 00:02:49,780
Bring it on.

31
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:50,419
Good.

32
00:02:50,780 --> 00:02:51,860
I'm asking then.

33
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:53,580
Go ahead.

34
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:54,740
There are two children.

35
00:02:56,219 --> 00:02:57,620
They go to the same school.

36
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,740
They live in the same alley.

37
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,419
When the two children go to school,

38
00:03:02,979 --> 00:03:04,180
one goes left out the door,

39
00:03:04,219 --> 00:03:05,539
and one goes right out the door.

40
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:06,500
What's going on here?

41
00:03:06,979 --> 00:03:08,219
That's too simple.

42
00:03:08,539 --> 00:03:09,500
These two students,

43
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,300
their homes,

44
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:11,539
one lives to the left of the school,

45
00:03:11,539 --> 00:03:12,780
and one lives to the right of the school.

46
00:03:12,780 --> 00:03:13,500
Wrong.

47
00:03:13,620 --> 00:03:15,180
The two children are neighbors.

48
00:03:15,259 --> 00:03:17,139
They're no more than two meters apart.

49
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:20,740
How is that possible?

50
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:21,539
You don't know, do you?

51
00:03:22,539 --> 00:03:24,020
The two kids live across from each other.

52
00:03:24,979 --> 00:03:26,180
Such a simple little question,

53
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:27,300
and you can't even answer it.

54
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,819
And you call yourself learned.

55
00:03:29,419 --> 00:03:30,219
That doesn't count.

56
00:03:30,819 --> 00:03:31,740
That's too misleading.

57
00:03:31,819 --> 00:03:33,060
Ask another one if you've got the guts.

58
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:33,520
Fine.

59
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,819
Then I'll ask another one.

60
00:03:35,939 --> 00:03:37,219
Old Zhang is reading in his room.

61
00:03:37,419 --> 00:03:39,060
Suddenly, the power goes out.

62
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,800
Why can Old Zhang keep reading?

63
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:43,259
This question is too childish.

64
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,759
Because it's daytime.

65
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:45,159
Right?

66
00:03:45,159 --> 00:03:45,699
Wrong.

67
00:03:45,819 --> 00:03:47,099
It's twelve o'clock at night.

68
00:03:47,419 --> 00:03:48,580
After the power goes out,

69
00:03:48,819 --> 00:03:50,539
you can't see your hand in front of your face.

70
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:52,340
But Old Zhang can still keep reading.

71
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,219
How is that possible?

72
00:03:53,219 --> 00:03:53,780
That's impossible.

73
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:54,740
Absolutely impossible.

74
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,379
Tell me why.

75
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,180
The answer definitely won't hold water.

76
00:03:58,419 --> 00:03:59,979
Old Zhang is blind.

77
00:03:59,979 --> 00:04:01,580
He's reading Braille.

78
00:04:03,860 --> 00:04:05,819
You can't even answer such a simple question.

79
00:04:05,819 --> 00:04:07,620
How did you do your studying?

80
00:04:07,659 --> 00:04:09,080
University, graduate school...

81
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,180
All for nothing.

82
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:11,680
You're worse than me, from the school of life,

83
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:12,479
a worker-peasant-soldier.

84
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:13,099
Honestly.

85
00:04:14,099 --> 00:04:16,160
Coming up with two brain teasers isn't a skill.

86
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,220
If you're capable, let's...

87
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:17,980
compete in something else.

88
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:18,939
Compete in something else?

89
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,459
What other skills do you have?

90
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,459
Besides spouting a few phrases of a foreign language,

91
00:04:22,459 --> 00:04:23,980
correcting a few typos,

92
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,699
and writing a few lousy critiques.

93
00:04:25,699 --> 00:04:27,259
Tell me, what other talents do you have?

94
00:04:27,259 --> 00:04:28,500
What else can you do?

95
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:31,420
I can do magic tricks.

96
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,459
I can make a living person disappear.

97
00:04:33,779 --> 00:04:35,399
I can channel my energy and make you vanish.

98
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,019
Do you believe me?

99
00:04:36,019 --> 00:04:37,379
I don't believe a word you say.

100
00:04:37,899 --> 00:04:40,220
This old man is very wicked.

101
00:04:42,139 --> 00:04:43,300
I'm a big living person.

102
00:04:43,339 --> 00:04:44,779
You can make me disappear?

103
00:04:44,939 --> 00:04:45,740
Did everyone hear that?

104
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:46,779
Professor Fan said,

105
00:04:46,779 --> 00:04:48,060
he can make me disappear.

106
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,220
What are you shouting for?

107
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:50,220
Scared?

108
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:51,180
Afraid to face the masses?

109
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:52,100
Who's scared?

110
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,160
If you're not scared, channel your energy.

111
00:04:53,379 --> 00:04:54,040
Do it.

112
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,220
Do it!

113
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:56,379
Fine, I'll do it.

114
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:58,420
But before I do, you have to cooperate with me.

115
00:04:58,420 --> 00:04:58,939
Cooperate how?

116
00:04:58,939 --> 00:05:00,220
Come on, um...

117
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:01,779
Stand with your legs straight.

118
00:05:02,259 --> 00:05:03,459
Shoulder-width apart.

119
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:04,980
Come on, squat down.

120
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,819
Thighs and calves at a right angle.

121
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,139
Isn't that just a horse stance?

122
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:10,139
Here, hold this book.

123
00:05:10,139 --> 00:05:10,660
Hold this book.

124
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:11,500
Pretend to read.

125
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,660
Why pretend?

126
00:05:12,899 --> 00:05:13,939
I'm actually reading.

127
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,060
This is an English book of mine.

128
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:16,220
You can't understand it anyway.

129
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:18,180
Fine.

130
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:19,459
I'm going to start channeling now.

131
00:05:19,459 --> 00:05:21,139
In the army, I could do this for an hour. Come on.

132
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:24,779
Hurry up

133
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:27,860
Done

134
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:29,980
Darn it

135
00:05:30,259 --> 00:05:31,139
I'm still right here

136
00:05:31,139 --> 00:05:32,420
Immovable

137
00:05:32,420 --> 00:05:33,459
Don't be impatient

138
00:05:33,459 --> 00:05:34,220
This power I'm channeling

139
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:35,500
Has a bit of a lag

140
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,899
You'll disappear completely in a minute

141
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:39,100
Let's time it now

142
00:05:39,259 --> 00:05:39,939
Hello, Old Zhang

143
00:05:39,939 --> 00:05:40,639
Alright

144
00:05:40,639 --> 00:05:41,860
One minute on the clock

145
00:05:42,139 --> 00:05:42,980
Start. Come on

146
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:43,519
Okay

147
00:05:43,899 --> 00:05:44,779
It's just one minute

148
00:05:44,779 --> 00:05:45,819
Channeling this power

149
00:05:45,819 --> 00:05:46,459
I can hold it

150
00:05:46,459 --> 00:05:46,939
I'm getting a bit tired

151
00:05:46,939 --> 00:05:47,980
I'm going to replenish my qi

152
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:48,740
Go ahead. Okay

153
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:49,939
You keep this pose

154
00:05:49,939 --> 00:05:50,439
Fine

155
00:05:50,439 --> 00:05:51,279
If you move, it won't work

156
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:51,819
Got it

157
00:05:51,819 --> 00:05:52,459
Okay, I'm going

158
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:53,860
Everyone watch, one minute

159
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:54,579
I haven't moved

160
00:05:54,579 --> 00:05:55,819
Haven't moved

161
00:05:56,819 --> 00:05:57,620
How is it?

162
00:05:58,180 --> 00:05:59,939
Hello comrades. Hello

163
00:05:59,939 --> 00:06:00,540
President Liang

164
00:06:01,740 --> 00:06:02,540
Boss Li

165
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,180
What kind of kung fu are you practicing?

166
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:04,939
He...

167
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:06,300
Professor Fan said

168
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,660
He can make a living person disappear

169
00:06:07,899 --> 00:06:09,579
Said if I stay still for a minute

170
00:06:09,899 --> 00:06:11,019
When he comes back in a bit

171
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:12,100
I'll have disappeared

172
00:06:13,379 --> 00:06:15,500
I don't think this looks like a disappearing act

173
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,259
What does it look like?

174
00:06:16,259 --> 00:06:18,019
You look like a living person taking a dump

175
00:06:21,139 --> 00:06:22,500
Alright, Old Fan

176
00:06:23,180 --> 00:06:24,540
You dare trick me

177
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:25,600
Watch how I...

178
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:27,339
I'm going to fix you good

179
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,300
Old Fan

180
00:06:28,579 --> 00:06:29,379
Old Fan

181
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:33,819
How did it go today? Who won?

182
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:39,420
Why you, Old Fan

183
00:06:40,180 --> 00:06:41,079
What's going on?

184
00:06:41,699 --> 00:06:42,500
Boss Li

185
00:06:42,579 --> 00:06:44,620
Why did you scare the girl away?

186
00:06:44,620 --> 00:06:45,439
Who scared...

187
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:47,579
I was just about to ask you

188
00:06:47,899 --> 00:06:49,279
Right, I was just about to ask you

189
00:06:49,779 --> 00:06:50,779
Why did you trick me?

190
00:06:52,339 --> 00:06:53,959
Happy April Fools' Day

191
00:06:54,660 --> 00:06:55,579
What are you cursing me?

192
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:57,699
Don't think I can't tell

193
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,779
Who cursed you?

194
00:06:58,779 --> 00:07:00,620
I'm wishing you a happy holiday

195
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:01,939
Who are you fooling?

196
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:03,860
It's still a month until May Day

197
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:05,459
Who said May Day?

198
00:07:05,579 --> 00:07:07,779
Today is April 1st, April Fools' Day

199
00:07:07,819 --> 00:07:09,300
In English, it's called April Fools'

200
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:10,339
And in French?

201
00:07:10,339 --> 00:07:11,339
Don't show off to me

202
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,259
I'm asking you why you tricked me

203
00:07:13,860 --> 00:07:14,819
April Fools' Day

204
00:07:15,139 --> 00:07:16,939
Is a holiday for pranks

205
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,660
You can't even take a joke

206
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:20,180
You're a sore loser

207
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:21,060
Who's a sore loser?

208
00:07:21,779 --> 00:07:23,339
What April Fools' Day pranks?

209
00:07:23,819 --> 00:07:25,660
Isn't it just everyone tricking each other?

210
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:26,660
You just wait

211
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:29,339
I'm going to trick you good today

212
00:07:42,339 --> 00:07:43,819
April Fools' Day

213
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,220
Just you watch.

214
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:52,899
I'm gonna prank you so hard today you'll foam at the mouth.

215
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:57,779
Hello, President Li.

216
00:07:58,379 --> 00:07:59,259
Xiao Chang.

217
00:08:00,779 --> 00:08:01,660
What are you doing?

218
00:08:02,819 --> 00:08:04,300
I felt a bit hungry.

219
00:08:04,579 --> 00:08:05,379
Having a snack.

220
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:06,819
Then what's this?

221
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:07,740
The toothpaste.

222
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,379
Eating cookies while...

223
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,899
...brushing my teeth.

224
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:14,860
How can you eat cookies while brushing your teeth?

225
00:08:14,939 --> 00:08:15,819
That's just it.

226
00:08:16,899 --> 00:08:18,180
Aren't these dentures?

227
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:20,339
Alright.

228
00:08:20,699 --> 00:08:21,699
President Li, let me introduce you.

229
00:08:21,699 --> 00:08:22,339
Director Xu.

230
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,199
This is Director Xu from the TV station.

231
00:08:28,139 --> 00:08:28,939
Hello, Director Xu.

232
00:08:28,939 --> 00:08:29,779
President Li.

233
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:30,980
No need to be so formal.

234
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,460
Just call me Xiao Xu.

235
00:08:32,460 --> 00:08:33,179
Young and promising.

236
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,120
Thank you.

237
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,100
Here's the thing.

238
00:08:35,179 --> 00:08:36,179
Our station...

239
00:08:36,179 --> 00:08:37,899
...has revamped the Life Channel.

240
00:08:38,139 --> 00:08:40,019
We came to the retirement community today...

241
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,299
...to look for inspiration.

242
00:08:42,379 --> 00:08:43,659
We have a program...

243
00:08:43,659 --> 00:08:45,000
called "Aging with Purpose."

244
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,500
Good.

245
00:08:45,779 --> 00:08:46,860
So...

246
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,919
You've heard all about my deeds.

247
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,500
I haven't done nearly enough.

248
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:55,500
In painting, I can't compare to Fan Zeng.

249
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:58,299
In calligraphy, I can't compare to Qi Gong.

250
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,139
In dancing, I can't compare to Yang Liping.

251
00:09:02,059 --> 00:09:04,860
In piano, I can't compare to Kong Xiangdong.

252
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,299
I am ashamed.

253
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,379
Listen to that.

254
00:09:08,259 --> 00:09:09,740
Mr. Li's standards for himself...

255
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,139
...are way too high.

256
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:12,740
Mr. Li.

257
00:09:12,899 --> 00:09:14,100
Don't be so formal with me.

258
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,419
Just call me President Li.

259
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:17,559
How is the lighting in this room?

260
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:19,059
Do I need to...

261
00:09:19,179 --> 00:09:19,960
...put on some makeup?

262
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,019
No...

263
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:22,480
President Li...

264
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:23,740
...you've misunderstood.

265
00:09:23,940 --> 00:09:25,259
We came here this time...

266
00:09:25,299 --> 00:09:27,659
...to look in this community...

267
00:09:27,659 --> 00:09:29,620
...for a highly respected guest.

268
00:09:29,620 --> 00:09:30,320
Yes.

269
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:30,840
Right?

270
00:09:31,139 --> 00:09:32,139
We're not recording here.

271
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:35,220
We want to take him...

272
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,639
...to our station...

273
00:09:36,899 --> 00:09:38,139
...to record there.

274
00:09:38,299 --> 00:09:39,299
Is that so?

275
00:09:39,299 --> 00:09:39,820
Then let's...

276
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:41,659
So the person we want to invite is your...

277
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,340
...roommate.

278
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:43,700
Right.

279
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:44,620
Professor Fan Dacheng.

280
00:09:44,759 --> 00:09:45,659
Yes.

281
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,200
Is that so

282
00:09:54,179 --> 00:09:55,419
It's actually okay

283
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:58,700
But about Professor Fan

284
00:09:58,860 --> 00:09:59,519
Boss Li

285
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,460
The TV station's car

286
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:02,620
Is waiting outside

287
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:03,379
Why don't you tell us

288
00:10:03,379 --> 00:10:04,659
Where Professor Fan went

289
00:10:05,179 --> 00:10:05,980
Where did he go

