582
00:19:29,019 --> 00:19:30,180
I heard Royal Physician Sun say

583
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:32,240
it seems they'll be ready this afternoon

584
00:19:36,059 --> 00:19:36,859
President Li

585
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,660
I finally found you

586
00:19:38,819 --> 00:19:40,779
Old Sun, what do you need me for?

587
00:19:42,319 --> 00:19:42,900
You...

588
00:19:43,619 --> 00:19:44,759
look at this X-ray

589
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:46,700
Here in the lungs

590
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,299
there's a noticeable shadow

591
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,299
Shadow

592
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:55,420
Isn't that cancer?

593
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:58,019
Someone pour me a glass of water.

594
00:19:58,019 --> 00:19:58,599
Hurry.

595
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:01,299
Royal Physician Sun.

596
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:03,140
Tell me the truth.

597
00:20:04,299 --> 00:20:05,819
How many days do I have left?

598
00:20:06,819 --> 00:20:07,619
Boss Li.

599
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:09,700
This film isn't yours.

600
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,980
It's Professor Fan Dacheng's.

601
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:14,259
It's not me?

602
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:15,880
That's great!

603
00:20:18,079 --> 00:20:19,319
No, it's not mine.

604
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,720
Then why did you show it to me?

605
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,059
I...

606
00:20:21,059 --> 00:20:22,200
You'll scare someone to death.

607
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,400
I came to ask you...

608
00:20:24,079 --> 00:20:26,119
...where Professor Fan Dacheng is right now.

609
00:20:26,119 --> 00:20:27,640
Aren't you roommates?

610
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:30,240
With this condition, he must be re-examined immediately.

611
00:20:32,359 --> 00:20:33,279
You guys keep playing.

612
00:20:33,279 --> 00:20:34,720
I need to go find Professor Fan right away.

613
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,079
Teacher Liu, play a couple of rounds for me.

614
00:20:36,079 --> 00:20:37,240
I don't know how.

615
00:20:37,519 --> 00:20:38,640
I don't know how.

616
00:20:39,519 --> 00:20:41,799
I mean, we should probably go over there too.

617
00:20:41,839 --> 00:20:42,440
Right.

618
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,799
Let's go check on him.

619
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,119
Let's stop playing for now.

620
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,200
This...

621
00:20:46,539 --> 00:20:46,940
This...

622
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,279
So the game's over?

623
00:20:50,279 --> 00:20:51,319
Fan...

624
00:20:52,039 --> 00:20:52,839
Professor Fan.

625
00:20:53,279 --> 00:20:54,599
Stop reading.

626
00:20:54,799 --> 00:20:55,880
Bad news.

627
00:20:56,539 --> 00:20:56,920
You...

628
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:57,960
Are you going to tell me...

629
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,440
...some unfortunate news again?

630
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,400
At a time like this...

631
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,759
...you're still joking around with me?

632
00:21:02,039 --> 00:21:02,759
This time, I really...

633
00:21:02,759 --> 00:21:04,200
...bring you unfortunate news.

634
00:21:04,359 --> 00:21:06,079
Royal Physician Sun just told me...

635
00:21:06,079 --> 00:21:07,319
...that your lungs...

636
00:21:07,319 --> 00:21:08,279
...have a shadow on them.

637
00:21:08,279 --> 00:21:10,160
He said to go to the Medical Center for a re-check.

638
00:21:10,799 --> 00:21:11,420
Oh my god!

639
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:12,519
Is it true?

640
00:21:12,519 --> 00:21:13,160
This...

641
00:21:13,279 --> 00:21:14,359
What are we going to do?

642
00:21:14,359 --> 00:21:16,799
Stop with your little tricks.

643
00:21:16,799 --> 00:21:19,359
Do you think I'm that easy to fool?

644
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,240
What tricks?

645
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,440
I'm telling you the absolute truth.

646
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,079
I must admit...

647
00:21:24,079 --> 00:21:25,400
...the lie you made up this time...

648
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,759
...is quite creative.

649
00:21:27,799 --> 00:21:28,640
It's quite sophisticated.

650
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,319
You really used your brain.

651
00:21:30,319 --> 00:21:31,400
But when it comes to fooling me...

652
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,000
...you'd better come up with a better plan.

653
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,720
What creativity?

654
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,519
Royal Physician Sun told me personally.

655
00:21:36,519 --> 00:21:38,359
He said there's a shadow on your lungs.

656
00:21:41,319 --> 00:21:42,220
Look.

657
00:21:42,319 --> 00:21:43,759
Is he here yet?

658
00:21:43,799 --> 00:21:45,839
Professor Fan, we finally found you.

659
00:21:45,839 --> 00:21:47,799
Hurry up, come with me to the Medical Center for a re-check.

660
00:21:47,839 --> 00:21:48,640
Royal Physician Sun,

661
00:21:49,279 --> 00:21:49,920
you, my elder,

662
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:52,160
such a highly respected gentleman,

663
00:21:52,319 --> 00:21:54,000
are joining him to trick me too?

664
00:21:54,319 --> 00:21:55,160
Naughty.

665
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,680
Professor Fan, we really aren't tricking you this time.

666
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,839
Old Liang, are you in on it with them too?

667
00:21:59,839 --> 00:22:00,920
Shut up, stop babbling.

668
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:01,660
Go to the hospital.

669
00:22:01,819 --> 00:22:02,980
I'm not going.

670
00:22:03,119 --> 00:22:04,519
I won't fall for it.

671
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,079
Stop wasting breath on him.

672
00:22:06,079 --> 00:22:07,000
Grab his arms and waist.

673
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,440
We're dragging him to the hospital today no matter what.

674
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:08,940
Okay.

675
00:22:09,359 --> 00:22:09,920
Don't.

676
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:10,839
Don't move.

677
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:11,759
You, surnamed Li!

678
00:22:11,759 --> 00:22:12,839
You can't play like this!

679
00:22:12,839 --> 00:22:14,079
No, Old Fan...

680
00:22:14,079 --> 00:22:14,759
Don't get excited.

681
00:22:14,759 --> 00:22:15,640
President Li really...

682
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:17,000
and all of us just mean well.

683
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,039
Come on, hurry up.

684
00:22:18,039 --> 00:22:19,519
What do you mean "mean well"?

685
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,720
I taught him about April Fools' Day, didn't I?

686
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:22,200
You guys...

687
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,319
Fine, everyone together.

688
00:22:23,319 --> 00:22:23,759
Get him!

689
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:24,640
Stop it!

690
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:25,319
What April Fools' Day?

691
00:22:25,319 --> 00:22:26,400
This April Fools' Day...

692
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,640
I'm telling you,

693
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,079
don't play with people's lives!

694
00:22:29,079 --> 00:22:29,680
Easy now.

695
00:22:30,039 --> 00:22:31,519
Easy! What are you doing?

696
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:32,799
Stop it!

697
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,480
It's for your own good.

698
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:36,000
You've all been tricked by Old Li!

699
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:37,640
Don't!

700
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,339
Seriously, stop messing around!

701
00:22:51,019 --> 00:22:53,779
I kind of understand you young people now.

702
00:22:54,059 --> 00:22:55,339
That Wu Di...

703
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,740
he doesn't have it easy either.

704
00:22:58,539 --> 00:22:59,460
Auntie Cai,

705
00:22:59,819 --> 00:23:01,299
you just went there once,

706
00:23:01,299 --> 00:23:02,859
and you've already defected to "Di"?

707
00:23:03,539 --> 00:23:04,599
It's not defecting.

708
00:23:04,799 --> 00:23:05,539
That "Di"...

709
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:07,539
he has his difficulties.

710
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,019
Child,

711
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:12,180
you have to cherish your school days.

712
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:14,299
Once you step into society,

713
00:23:14,539 --> 00:23:16,740
you have to fend for yourself entirely.

714
00:23:16,819 --> 00:23:18,299
You can't count on your parents.

715
00:23:19,099 --> 00:23:21,539
Wu Di was determined to break up with Xiao Xin.

716
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,940
There's no way to salvage it now.

717
00:23:27,059 --> 00:23:28,259
I didn't complete the mission.

718
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:29,019
I don't even know

719
00:23:29,019 --> 00:23:30,720
how to explain it to Xiao Xin.

720
00:23:31,099 --> 00:23:31,900
Okay.

721
00:23:32,180 --> 00:23:33,460
He added me back.

722
00:23:33,460 --> 00:23:35,059
We aren't breaking up anymore.

723
00:23:35,059 --> 00:23:36,339
For real?

724
00:23:36,339 --> 00:23:37,259
What's the situation?

725
00:23:37,299 --> 00:23:38,420
What happened?

726
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:39,180
Tell us.

727
00:23:39,299 --> 00:23:40,099
Wu Di said

728
00:23:40,099 --> 00:23:42,579
he received some profound education today,

729
00:23:42,579 --> 00:23:45,059
and decided never to give up, no matter how hard it gets.

730
00:23:45,059 --> 00:23:46,660
He'll stay with me through thick and thin.

731
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:12,859
You old rascal.

732
00:24:12,859 --> 00:24:14,380
You actually came back?

733
00:24:14,380 --> 00:24:15,200
Look at you.

734
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:18,140
You just ruled out the possibility of lung cancer,

735
00:24:18,140 --> 00:24:19,380
and now you're blowing your top again.

736
00:24:19,779 --> 00:24:21,460
That's really bad for your health.

737
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:23,140
Besides, what did I do to you today?

738
00:24:23,140 --> 00:24:25,059
You really tricked me today.

739
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:26,940
I didn't trick you today.

740
00:24:26,940 --> 00:24:28,460
Every word I said was the truth.

741
00:24:28,819 --> 00:24:30,299
That is a trick!

742
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:32,539
You said you were going to trick me today,

743
00:24:32,539 --> 00:24:34,299
but you actually didn't trick me.

744
00:24:34,299 --> 00:24:35,940
That is the biggest trick of all!

745
00:24:35,940 --> 00:24:37,140
You went back on your word!

746
00:24:37,579 --> 00:24:38,599
I said I'd trick you,

747
00:24:38,779 --> 00:24:39,700
but I didn't trick you,

748
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:40,819
yet you were tricked.

749
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,180
I kept my word.

750
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:43,819
How can you say I went back on my word?

751
00:24:44,259 --> 00:24:45,900
Tricking you with lies...

752
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:46,579
that...

753
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,019
isn't real skill.

754
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:50,339
It doesn't show Boss Li's true mastery.

755
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,299
So?

756
00:24:52,819 --> 00:24:53,619
Impressed?

757
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:01,579
Serves you right.

758
00:25:01,579 --> 00:25:03,059
Choked on my biscuit, didn't you?

759
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:05,339
Luckily, I learned the Heimlich maneuver.

760
00:25:06,059 --> 00:25:07,000
Move! Quick, move!

761
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:15,859
Boss Li, how are you?

762
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,220
Is it serious?

763
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:18,980
Should we call Royal Physician Sun?

764
00:25:21,819 --> 00:25:22,940
Don't call Royal Physician Sun.

765
00:25:23,079 --> 00:25:24,059
I only have myself to blame.

766
00:25:28,859 --> 00:25:30,539
In that biscuit I gave you this morning,

767
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:31,859
I squeezed a tube of toothpaste.
